ource";s:97:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/hydroborationoxidation-borane-alkene-alignment--614248836658794705/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:58:{i:0;s:73:"To gain more stability cyclohexane adopts the chair conformation instead.";i:1;s:155:"The chair conformation is a six-membered ring in which atoms 2 3 5 and 6 lie in the same plane atom 1 lies above the plane and atom 4 lies below the plane.";i:2;s:94:"With this conformation the bond angles are 1109 degrees much closer to the ideal 1095 degrees.";i:3;s:131:"The chair conformation is more stable because it does not have any steric hindrance or steric repulsion between the hydrogen bonds.";i:4;s:84:"By drawing cyclohexane in a chair conformation we can see how the Hs are positioned.";i:5;s:38:"These are hydrogens in the axial form.";i:6;s:42:"These hydrogens are in an equitorial form.";i:7;s:38:"Why are chairs more stable than boats.";i:8;s:114:"So choosing the more stable chair conformation is straightforward when there is only one group on the cyclohexane.";i:9;s:59:"You just need to find the energy value for the axial group.";i:10;s:121:"However if there are more groups on the cyclohexane we need to take into consideration the 13-diaxial interaction of all.";i:11;s:180:"However do I prioritize Cl over the methyl-and isopropyl-group or are the two groups more prioritized due to them being bonded to Hydrogens which take up more space than a Cl-atom.";i:12;s:117:"From what I have read I would say that the chair conformation on the top is the most stable prioritizing the methyl-.";i:13;s:50:"Thereof why is the chair conformation more stable.";i:14;s:131:"The chair conformation is more stable because it does not have any steric hindrance or steric repulsion between the hydrogen bonds.";i:15;s:84:"By drawing cyclohexane in a chair conformation we can see how the Hs are positioned.";i:16;s:38:"These are hydrogens in the axial form.";i:17;s:81:"In cyclohexane and most of its derivatives the c