which would be 1109 degreesDue to this the strain reduces and results in a lowered energy.";i:37;s:262:"Chair conformation of cyclohexane is more stable than boat form because in chair conformaion the C-H bonds are equally axial and equatorial ie out of twelve C-H bonds six are axial and six are equatorial and each carbon has one axial and one equatorial C-H bond.";i:38;s:248:"It turns out that a chair conformation minimizes what are called transannular interactions in that each carbon on the ring as an axial hydrogen projecting out of the plane of the ring or an equatorial hydrogen more or less in the plane of the ring.";i:39;s:92:"When the ring flips conformation the axial substitutent swaps positions with the equatorial.";i:40;s:96:"Although it is more stable the chair conformation is much more rigid than the boat conformation.";i:41;s:40:"The boat conformation is quite flexible.";i:42;s:168:"By flexing to a new formthe twist conformation Fig5the boat conformation can relieve some of its torsional strain and at the same time reduce the flagpole interactions.";i:43;s:131:"The chair conformation is more stable because it does not have any steric hindrance or steric repulsion between the hydrogen bonds.";i:44;s:119:"Of these two positions of the Hs the equitorial form will be the most stable because the hydrogen atoms or perhaps the.";i:45;s:32:"Chemistry questions and answers.";i:46;s:81:"Which chair structure depicts the most stable conformation of the molecule shown.";i:47;s:67:"Appropriate toHindicate the least and most stable chair conformers.";i:48;s:106:"Assuming that A values are additive and hence subtractive if necessary predict what the ΔG value will be.";i:49;s:156:"6 pt Cl Least stable chair Most stable chair 1 1 1 CH3G kcalmol e For the isomer of 1-chloro-35-dimethylcyclohexane shown below draw in bonds to CH3 and Cl.";i:50;s:94:"A chair conformation is one of many conformations of a cyclohexane ring and it is most stable.";i:51;s:34:"It has equatorial and axial bonds.";i:52;s:122:"The equatorial bonds e are perpendicular to the axis of the ring while axial bonds a are parallel to the axis of the ring.";i:53;s:65:"Select both chair conformations of cis-13-diisopropylcyclohexane.";i:54;s:80:"Ly d Select the more stable chair conformation of cis-13-diisopropylcyclohexane.";i:55;s:90:"Ly 크 Practice the Skill 04081 Provide a systematic name of the following compound below.";i:56;s:65:"Select both chair conformations of cis-13-diisopropylcyclohexane.";i:57;s:57:"Ly d Select the more stable chair conformation of cis-13.";}}